You are given the head of a singly linked list, you have to left rotate the linked list k times. Return the head of the modified linked list.

input nodes : 10 -> 20 -> 30 -> 40 -> 50
k = 4
output: 50 -> 10 -> 20 -> 30 -> 40

TC : O(n) + O(k%n) => O(N)
SC : O(1)
Approach: Circular Linked List Shifting
/*
class Node {
    int data;
    Node next;

    Node(int d){
        data=d;
        next=null;
   }
}
*/

class Solution {
    public Node rotate(Node head, int k) {
        // Base case
        if (head == null || head.next == null || k == 0) return head;
        
        // Step 1: Find the length of the linked list
        int length = 1;
        Node temp = head;
        while (temp.next != null) {
            temp = temp.next;
            length++;
        }
        
        // Step 2: if k >= length
        k = k % length;
        if (k == 0) return head; // No rotation needed
        
        // Step 3: circular list
        temp.next = head; 
        
        // Step 4: Traverse to the k-th node
        temp = head;
        for (int i = 1; i < k; i++) {
            temp = temp.next;
        }
        
        // Step 5:  
        Node newHead = temp.next; // store k'th next element
        temp.next = null;  // make k'th next element null
        
        return newHead;
    }
}
